description:
This package provides [Auto], [AutoParent] and [AutoChildren] attributes. 

They allow to automatically get/fetch references of components at the very start of the application. 

Using auto, getting your components is as simple as preprending the appropriate [Auto*] attribute to your variable declarations. 

Auto can be used with all access modifiers (private, protected, public), and all types (Unity components and custom monobehaviours). 

[AutoParent] and [AutoChildren] can be used either to get a single component, or get all the components as an array. 

Here are a couple of examples: 

[Auto] public Rigidbody myRb; 

[AutoParent] protected Collider[] myParentsColliders; 

[AutoChildren] private CustomScript scriptInOneOfChildren;
